	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's much easier to port a Disk System game to the NES if you give it WRAM.  In Zelda, most of the WRAM is devoted to holding a code bank, very little of it is for saved games.  And the prototype version of SMB2 was MMC1 with WRAM and CHR RAM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
